nized the james river chapter of the thoroughbred retirement foundation the local trf committee supports “greener pastures a rehabilitation and training program for inmates at james river work center using retired racehorses that are maintained at the prison robin was later elected to two terms as president of the national thoroughbred retirement foundation which supports nearly  rescued exracehorses in 3 states robin serves as a member of the board of directors of essex bank and its holding company community bankers trust corp robin is married and has a grown daughter as well as a flock of cats dogs and horses she likes to ride and work in the garden she is a recovering craftoholic whats everybody laughing about “this is hilarious stuff…be prepared to laugh out loud” the waltons creator earl hamner “more funny stories from the country seinfeld” sneaky pie author rita mae brown “…a humorous touch as light as a good soufflé…”  syndicated columnist james j kilpatrick “…the only time i stopped smiling was when i broke out laughing…”  syndicated columnist guy friddell “…thoroughly fun reading…real life fun stories escapades and common sense observations of life…” george allen former governor of virginia i laughed out loud and am still chuckling days later i like okra but had no idea what could be done with it thanks for amusing entertaining enlightening me robert c vaughan iii president virginia foundation for the humanities “…the country seinfeld read this book whoop and hollar and have a great time”  sneaky pie author rita mae brown webmail    login copyright 03  robin traywick williams all rights reserved website designed by fresh start design studio photo galleries  robintwilliamscom keep in touch   bush hogs  other swine chivalry thy name is bubba bio books home bloghiveadventures books stores photos awards links contact photo galleries animals just for fun the great outdoors my travels whats everybody laughing about “this is hilarious stuff…be prepared to laugh ou